            "title": "Rosalvo Florentino de Souza : um intelectual a servi\u00e7o do magist\u00e9rio na imprensa paulista (1949 a 1957)",
            "abstract": [
                "\u201cStating that Rosalvo Florentino de Souza is an intellectual at the service of education may seem strange, since, even though he wrote for two decades in the newspaper A Gazeta, from 1949 to 1968, according to the collection of clippings that were at the Instituto of Educational Studies \u201cSud Mennucci\u201d, on themes related to education, even having participated as a member and as founder of several class entities linked to education, even having been a secondary teacher, is not found in the literature on the History of Education, either in Brazil , whether from the State of S\u00e3o Paulo, any reference to it. It was from a survey carried out by an undergraduate student on certain newspaper clippings left by him at the Institute of Educational Studies \u201cSud Mennucci\u201d, that, through professor and researcher Rosa F\u00e1tima de Souza Chaloba, I became aware of the legacy left by this Bahian born in Caetit\u00e9\u201d.  There is hard work, serious research and devotion to education and teaching in this thesis book. Professor Glauco Bastos brings, through an immersion in time-worn documents, an intellectual look - Rosalvo Florentino de Souza - on the school culture of the 1940s to 1960s. the History of Brazilian Education and, even more, to fill invaluable gaps in public education policies in S\u00e3o Paulo at the time studied. Through a work based on Sherlock Holmes, Glauco Bastos brilliantly appropriates articles written by columnist Rosalvo Florentino in the newspaper \u201cA Gazeta\u201d to present us with an extraordinary piece for understanding the many paths taken by the national teaching profession up to the present day. Finally, academia and the general public find this book a unique source of research and the certainty of a fruitful and enjoyable reading",
                "\u201cAfirmar que Rosalvo Florentino de Souza \u00e9 um intelectual a servi\u00e7o da educa\u00e7\u00e3o pode parecer estranho, uma vez que, mesmo tendo escrito por duas d\u00e9cadas no jornal A Gazeta, de 1949 a 1968, de acordo com a cole\u00e7\u00e3o de recortes que se encontravam no Instituto de Estudos Educacionais \u201cSud Mennucci\u201d, sobre temas relacionados \u00e0 educa\u00e7\u00e3o, mesmo tendo participado como membro e como fundador de diversas entidades de classe ligadas \u00e0 educa\u00e7\u00e3o, mesmo tendo sido professor secund\u00e1rio, n\u00e3o se encontra na literatura sobre Hist\u00f3ria da Educa\u00e7\u00e3o, seja do Brasil, seja do Estado de S\u00e3o Paulo, qualquer refer\u00eancia a ele. Foi a partir de um levantamento feito por uma aluna de gradua\u00e7\u00e3o sobre certos recortes de jornais deixados por ele no Instituto de Estudos Educacionais \u201cSud Mennucci\u201d, que, por interm\u00e9dio da professora e pesquisadora Rosa F\u00e1tima de Souza Chaloba, tomei conhecimento do legado deixado por esse baiano nascido em Caetit\u00e9\u201d.  H\u00e1 neste livro-tese trabalho \u00e1rduo, pesquisa s\u00e9ria e devo\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e0 educa\u00e7\u00e3o e ao ensino. O professor Glauco Bastos traz, atrav\u00e9s de uma imers\u00e3o em documentos gastos pelo tempo, um olhar do intelectual - Rosalvo Florentino de Souza \u2013 sobre a cultura escolar dos idos anos de 1940 a 1960. Esta obra ratifica a relev\u00e2ncia da pesquisa documental para que se compreenda a Hist\u00f3ria da Educa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira e, mais ainda, para que se preencham lacunas inestim\u00e1veis de pol\u00edticas p\u00fablicas de ensino em S\u00e3o Paulo \u00e0 \u00e9poca estudada. Por meio de um trabalho a Sherlock Holmes, Glauco Bastos se apropria brilhantemente de mat\u00e9rias escritas pelo articulista Rosalvo Florentino no jornal \u201cA Gazeta\u201d para nos presentear com uma pe\u00e7a extraordin\u00e1ria para o entendimento dos muitos caminhos percorridos pelo magist\u00e9rio nacional at\u00e9 os dias atuais. Enfim, a academia e o p\u00fablico em geral t\u00eam neste livro fonte de pesquisa \u00edmpar e certeza de uma leitura prof\u00edcua e agrad\u00e1vel"
            ],
